<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 2:43PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
central Roanoke and northeastern Montgomery Counties, the City of
Salem and the City of Roanoke through 315 PM EDT...
At 242 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Glenvar, or near Salem, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Catawba...
Glenvar...
Mc Donalds Mill...
and Hollins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
